## Keyword Assignment Validation

Before building any page, validate:

- [ ] Primary keyword assigned
- [ ] Secondary keywords listed (3-5 max)
- [ ] Keyword not cannibalized by another page
- [ ] Search intent matches page type
- [ ] Metadata template applied with keywords
- [ ] Current ranking position documented as baseline

---

## Performance Tracking

### Weekly Monitoring

- Position changes for P1 keywords
- CTR changes for optimized pages
- Impressions for new keyword targets

### Monthly Review

- Compare clicks/impressions vs. pre-migration baseline
- Identify keywords needing further optimization
- Update strategy based on performance data

### Quarterly Assessment

- Full keyword ranking report
- ROI analysis: Traffic change vs. revenue impact
- Strategy adjustments for next quarter

---

## Integration with Content Specifications

The Keyword Strategy informs Content Specifications:

1. Primary keyword → H1 and meta title
2. Secondary keywords → Body content and H2s where natural
3. Underserved keywords → Inform new page creation priorities
4. Metadata templates → Direct application in build

All content created must reference this document for keyword assignment before writing.
